OL,3,CPerseid meteor shower: When and where
OL,4,Cto see up to 100 meteors every hour
OL,6,FThe event is associated with the dusty
OL,7,Fdebris left by Comet Swift-Tuttle,
OL,8,Fwhich orbits the sun once every 133
OL,9,Fyears.
OL,11,FThe meteoroids from the comet, mostly
OL,12,Fno bigger than a grain of sand, burn
OL,13,Fup as they hit the Earth's atmosphere
OL,14,Fat 36 miles per second, to produce a
OL,15,Fshooting stream of light in the sky.
OL,17,FPeak temperatures can reach anywhere
OL,18,Ffrom 1,648C to 5,537C as they hit the
OL,19,Fatmosphere.
